Abandoned Job/Communication Issues Most of the clients get frustrated when freelancers do not update them regarding the job’s progress. You need to be persistent in communicating with them to avoid misunderstandings. If there is a disagreement regarding the amount of job, explain yourself respectfully that you cannot make it and contact the customer support so they can assist them right away. Do not wait for several hours in order to resolve the issue.
2) Client’s Reason for Refund: Plagiarized Document

Save a copy of a plagiarism checker result of the output you have submitted to the client to assure that it is your original work. Do not forge the result and provide the evidence for the whole document.
3) Client’s Reason for Refund: Did not meet the deadline.

Getting projects completed within the provided timeline is the reason for hiring freelancers. You need to submit the output ahead of time. If the application is having issues, reach out to the customer support via email at support@24task.com and request them to send the files directly to the client.
4) Client’s Reason for Refund: Not satisfied with the Work Quality.

Projects do not only work with the intention of getting the output done before the deadline. You should also provide a high-quality result of the output. It is important to set a standard on the document you are producing and make sure that it meets the requirements. You need to be proactive in asking questions to the client to avoid misunderstandings. Most of the clients are still students so you need to ask them carefully regarding the instructions and the topics you are dealing with.

Take note that you are accountable for the outputs you are submitting. It is your responsibility to resolve the client’s concerns while you are doing their task. If there is any conflict, misunderstandings or issues you cannot handle, contact the customer support department at https://nojom.com/contact-us
